name: Bambini
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Had an amazing experience here. I don‚Äôt get why there any bad reviews. The food was actually AMAZING, so fresh and so good & we tried a variety of different dishes.The vibes were 10/10, service was 10/10 and the live music was beautiful. The only thing is that you can‚Äôt see the Eiffel Tower from most of the tables, only a few in a small corner offer those views for dinner. But that didn‚Äôt take away from our experience at all. We‚Äôll definitely be back here, loved it!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The hype is real! Fantastic ambience and service. Live music and great food! The restaurant is beautiful, they have nice servers and talented artists performing. We had also a nice Eiffel Tower view. I enjoyed this place a lot. I‚Äôm picky with my Italian food, specially with tiramis√π (I‚Äôd suggest to share it, it‚Äôs a huge portion for a single person). I will definitely come back!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Last minute reservation made after seeing this restaurant recommend on tiktok. The pizza was big and filling, the decor and room was nice but was very pricey. Little attentions to detail such as the branded ice cube was nice. Seems to be an influencers heaven with girls taking photos with large LED lights throughout the whole night.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "I had higher expectations from this restaurant. The service was unfriendly; the waitress kept mentioning how expensive it was, which I found inappropriate. A server shouldn't judge patrons based on perceived affordability; politeness should be universal. It felt like she'd only be kind if she thought you'd leave a big tip. Additionally, the food wasn't tasty.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very nice place, views and service. The best apperol spritz in paris by far and the green bean salad is a must. The food is pretty good but a bit overpriced in my opinion. Would definitely recommend for a one time ocasion.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Afrodisiac Paris 2
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Real West-African food. Very good. I have been there three times. One time, lamb. Second time fish with rice. Last time fish with banana. Very tasteful. People are very friendly.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'my boyfriend comes from Senegal and we would like to visit some nice african restaurant in Paris. After searching google we found this restaurant. Looks very sophisticated with tasteful decor.

real world was totally different.
- we had to sit very narros between other customers, event though the service person didn¬¥t ask us whether it is fine for us.

- for washing my hands
the WC is the highlight, no sope, toilet paper around without fixing, dirty in side, smells like drain. the restaurant was not busy at all, but no one cares about it. I already lost my appetite.

- food
was not warm enough, I had seafood grill plate. the corn was bad so I spitted out and very salty.

the price range is quite high, so I would never ever visit this restaurant with that price.

Please go others.', 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Good food , bad service . They run out of beef and brought fish pastel to my friend without asking , not enough variety of dessert. They don‚Äôt take credit card', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great african food  the only reason why its not a 5 star is because the food is way too expensive for the small portion served. Not enough food per dish!!', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Food was fantastic and the staff was really helpful. Nice upscale decor.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Quai Nedy
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Best brunch in Paris

I had the Eiffel tour en plat and the blue dragon as a drink
It was incredible.
The service was also amazing,
It‚Äôs really chill chic and nice !
Highly recommend \U0001f90d', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Owner very Nice. New spot in Paris 16th facing the Eiffel tower. Cosy n warm place. Good To come with friends and better To book your table. The dishes are yummy, tasty...', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Going there for a hooka is good enough, but i do not recommend this place for the restaurant.
The food does not match with the pictures you can see online/Instagram. The avocado salad was not sliced but smashed, the multicoloured tomato salad with burrata was cold (from the fridge) and done with regular red tomatoes. The main course's portions are pretty small and not tasty for the price requested.

I was also pretty intrigued when i asked for a jug of water and the waitress told me they do not serve this kind of drink, which implies that i have to buy a bottle of water when I know its not legal to refuse tap water in restaurants in France.

I might come back for a hooka but certainly never for the restaurant.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'One of the best places I‚Äôve ever been in paris. The food is soooooo yummy. The staff are amazingly friendly and nice. Don‚Äôt forget to try the tiramisu. It‚Äôs very delicious. And shafik is one of the best person that could attend to you. Try it you won‚Äôt regret.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Nice place near the Eiffel Tower', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: YSL Cafe

name: Ravioli Folie
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent value for the price!  The place is beautiful, service is quick, and the food, especially the bao and shrimp bites, is really good.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The food was nice but the price is very expensive for the size of the portion. This is a much more student vibe with young people than I expected so be aware if you‚Äôre thinking this will be a quiet dinner. name: JJAN
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'The food was very good, very close to authentic and the price for a Korean restaurant in Paris was quite ‚Äúaffordable‚Äù. The portions are big so it fills you well. It is a very popular restaurant so it gets crowded (even waiting lines outside) and there isn‚Äôt much space between tables. The staff is really nice and accommodating, if you need anything just ask and they will bring you.
Definitely recommend!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very good Korean dishes‚Äîtwo pages of choices. Love my spicy tofu soup. They need more vegetarian choices. The bibimbap bowl should be much hotter as the rice was room temperature so it made the dish less exciting.  Spartan furniture.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Newly opened. Very tasty in a nicely designed restaurant.

Food wise : we got the dish to share. Cheese + chicken, some KFC as well.
It‚Äôs all good. Loved the fried chicken with their honey soy sauce.
Of course, they‚Äôll let you take everything in takeaway if you don‚Äôt finish.

Service wise : they just opened, when it‚Äôs full it gets a bit slow but I‚Äôm sure they‚Äôll improve very soon.

Price wise : I found it very affordable for that kind of Korean cuisine, especially considering it‚Äôs located in the very center of Paris.

I do recommend it.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great prices and great location. Small menu. We got the KFC and Budae Jigae- KFC was great and crispy and juicy. Budae came with two rice and we added spice so that was great. Nice sauce and was not too bad, 7/10. Service was quick.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Food looks delicious but is somehow tasteless.
The kimchi pancake is extra oily.
The service was nice and friendly.
Overall atmosphere is loud and fun, good for an affordable dinner with friends if you are in the area and don‚Äôt care much for the food quality.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: C√àPE ET FIGUE
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'We loved eating at this restaurant! I think we were lucky to get a table as it became very busy after we arrived. The food was delicious- very good quality. Even more exceptional was the service. They were very friendly and patient , despite our lack of French language skills. We later learned that it‚Äôs a family business, which just adds to the charm. Their set menu is good value for the quality of the dining experience.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent food and service. For appetizers we tried the burrata, escargots, and l‚Äô≈ìuf cocotte - all were great. For the main dish we got L‚Äôagneau - which was cooked 7 hours and tasted sublime (although I usually don‚Äôt eat much lamb). Le poulet and le boeuf bourguignon were amazing as well. The ambience is cozy and welcoming - best to reserve a table ahead of time as it tends to be busy.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing little restaurant in St Germaine. The food is some of the best we ate in the area. The staff are all charming and helped us with the translation as the menu has some great takes on traditional French cuisine.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Easily one of the best French restaurants in Paris. The dishes and the desserts are exceptional. Very affordable price for such high quality food. I recommend!
Food ordered: comme une poule au pot, agneau, fondant au chocolat, and crumble', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Of all the times I‚Äôve been in Paris, this is the best Parisian food I‚Äôve had. I found this place just like that and I didn‚Äôt regret it.

Me and my husband chose the three course menu (29‚Ç¨ great price!) and it was just heaven. The onion soup felt like a grandma soup, the lamb was so soft and tasty and the dessert was just amazing.

Please come to this place! The food and the service is great, very very recommended.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Libshop
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'The dishes are delicious and plentiful, the service is always pleasant and efficient. One of the best places in the neighborhood for lunch, even late. I recommend !', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very good Lebanese sandwich, the baked sweet potato and hummus are delicious', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I love it, the sandwiches are excellent! name: BOOM BOOM VILLETTE
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'This review is for Street Banh Mi at the Food Market. Follow a very good review of Vietnamese community group on Facebook, I gave it a try to support my homeland foods and restaurant owners. I tried their special ‚ÄúB√°nh m√¨ ch·∫£o‚Äù which is kind of double price of a normal b√°nh m√¨ 8,5‚Ç¨. And that‚Äôs already expensive compared to many good banh m√¨ that I have tried in Paris. It was very noisy there and we needed to wait a bit long. And the ‚ÄúB√°nh m√¨ ch·∫£o‚Äù is too far from the b√°nh m√¨ ch·∫£o that I know. Dry, no sauce and quantity is not up to the price 15‚Ç¨. The quality is average. And the bread is under baked, white, too soft not crunchy. I usually don‚Äôt spend time to write negative review. I did this time because it isn‚Äôt correct to serve average quality for high price.\nIt deserves 2,5 stars.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A very well conceptualised food court with lots of of options. They have bars,burgers,Asian and Indian food. You can visit it before or after a movie as pathe gaumont is on the same building.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We came here to treat the kids to a morning of fun amidst a busy week of visits in Paris, lured by the prospect of lots of entertainment for them and a nice lunch in the food court. But when we got there, everything but the food court and the cinema was closed - apparently the kids activies won‚Äôt open before a couple of weeks. You would think that‚Äôs something worth mentioning on their website before having people trek all the way to La Villette for nothing! Yet another soulless place where the emphasis is making money. Such a let down.', 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Kind of expensive for the small size of the portions and low quality of the food. It's just pre-made industrial food reheated in a fancy microwave priced like a normal restaurant. Not worth it.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This review is for Pokke restaurant at Boom Boom villette. Very slow service and they mixed up with our order and gave it to another person. Waited 30 minutes for one bowl.', 'rating': '2', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Genki ÂÖÉÊ∞ó
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Delicious tea and bubble tea, and deserts to die for. The hot green jasmine tea with tapioca was so great for the cold winter of our visit to Paris.
The atmosphere has a nice sophisticated minimalist style and the service was very nice as well on both times that we visited.

They also serve Chinese food, but we didn‚Äôt have an opportunity to try it. Next time for sure! :)', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This place is amazing. Very aesthetically pleasing as it is very minimalistic. Very luminous. The sitting is comfy and open. We ordered 4 different cakes and a drink : a basque cheesecake, a matcha mille crepe, an oreo and coconut cake, a mango cake and finally a mango frapp√©. They were all very tasty, the matcha mille crepe wasn‚Äôt too heavy nor sugary; the basque cheesecake is literally the best I found in Paris so far and not too sugary either. The mango cake is also light and flavourful. The oreo coco cake is the most sugary here and it was still very good. The drink was very refreshing even in this cold weather I would recommend. The service was very nice, the drinks are made in front of your eyes and the wait isn‚Äôt long at all. Owner very sweet and asks for advices on the cakes ! I recommend.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I order a strawberry cake and it was so tasty and fresh.
I took one star because the service is so slow.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "You won't regret trying this place.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "I had the fraise cheese. The best strawberry boba that I've ever had in any country I've been to. Wennic Greeted me with a smile and kept that smile the whole time we were there.  Amazing service, amazing place.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Pasticeria Simona
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'We found this place through "Paris food trip". Out of all the places we visited on the food trip, I think this was my favorite. Crazy Italian pastry shop in the middle of Paris. Love everything about it. From the pastry chef util the delicious cake we tasted.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Authentic Italian pastry, amazing coffee and a cozy atmosphere. Just perfection.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The cannolo was good, but I‚Äôve tasted the best in Italy. Well, we‚Äôre in France not Italy, so can‚Äôt really compare. Since it‚Äôs called pasticceria, I was expecting bomboloni or donut but too bad there‚Äôs nothing like that. The cafe is small, only about 8 people max, however there are some seating outside. I would like to point out their hygiene, cz they serve the pastry with bare hands, no thongs whatsoever. We never know what did they touch before, especially that the pandemic is still there and another whatever disease around. Hopefully next time they take care more in hygiene part.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very delicious patisserie. She helped make my boyfriend a delicious personalized cake, thank you it was so good!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'One of the best places to find authentic Italian pastries!! Must try their Maritozzo and Biaocchi!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: KINGKONG
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'We tried a few dishes. Considering everything was prepared very quickly. Fried chicken wings were spicy buy had a very nice sweet glaze, super crunchy. Tteokbokki had interesting flavors, tasted like tajin but with extra spice. Bibimbap was good, but the sauce was very mild.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This restaurant is quite well hidden in a small street near metro station Strasbourg Saint-Denis. By the look of the exterior I probably wouldn‚Äôt have entered had I not checked Google reviews before‚Ä¶ as the decor was somber and didn‚Äôt give an appetizing look to be honest.

However the food proved me wrong, we ordered lunch menu with the fried chicken as starter and bibimbap as main dish. The fried chicken was divine! So juicy and not greasy at all, the sweet and slightly spicy sauce blended perfectly with the batter, very delicious! The bibimbap itself was great too, it contained lots of ingredients especially vegetables, as they continued to cook in the stone ball they created a nice texture and taste together with the rice. I ordered the squid one, I should maybe have taken the beef and porc version as the squid was a bit chewy and not a lot of flavor. The other small negative point was probably that they were not very generous with the the pickled side dishes (see photo).

Overall I had a good dining experience and will definitely go back to try other dishes.

Update: we went back for the fried chicken and rice sticks, super delicious and you wouldn‚Äôt tell they were deep fried! Loved them.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Really good place that serve authentic korean dishes!

Definitely a must take: the korean fried chicken, it was crispy and juicy.

Loved the kimchi fried rice with sea food, I would love to have some seaweed on it to be 100% matching with that I got in Korea!

Moreover great beer selection!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great place for late night eating or drinking, korean cuisine is not only about the bbq, kingkong is more like street style korean food with a nice atmosphere, kpop music and great customer service. The man (the owner maybe) was super friendly. Army stew was flavourful and very filling. I didn‚Äôt like the fried chicken very much, properly because of the sauce. The soft tofu stew (sundubu) is also average. All in all, great restaurant to try out and also their menu changes from time to time so it‚Äôs worth a comeback', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Unfortunately, they stopped serving their corndogs, but the food was delicious all the same! A nice Korean restaurant near Sentier, with a cool upstairs ambiance. Recommended!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Trantranzai
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'I love coming here for their Dan Dan noodles, they never disappoint. You can get them with our without soup, and both versions are good!

If you don‚Äôt do that well with spice, don‚Äôt worry, you can select your spice range from 0-6. I personally go for level 2, which is still somewhat spicy and gives you a bit of that Szechuan tingle. My girlfriend who is Korean and loves spice opts for level 4, to give you a reference!

I also recommend the cucumber salad, and the dumplings. Both are very fresh and delicious.

The best part is everything g is quite cheap, especially for the quality of what you get. My Dan Dan noodles were only 12.80‚Ç¨.

And if you can‚Äôt tell from the photos and videos, the vibe is very fun and very cool. The service was good, and quick. Definitely check it out!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Really busy but we waited all of 5 minutes. Food is as good as it looks online. Staff were nice, but busy. Food was served promptly and the atmosphere is just the icing on the cake.

Bubble tea peach was amazing. Only suggestion is to sell the merchandise. Shirts and tote bags on display were not for sale but so cute!!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Definitely an extremely busy place and expect to wait for at least 30 min for a table on weekends. The hand pulled noodles are chewy and delicious and the beef was so tender. Cucumber side salad and dumplings were also amazing.

Must visit!!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "It was good, it's just a tiny bit disappointing how there aren't lots of options on the menu. We had vegetarian noodles and asked if they could add a shrimp supplement but they said it wasn't possible.

Nonetheless, we enjoyed our meal. It's wasn't very fulfilling, there was more broth than noodles.", 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very tasty food here.

I went for the ravioli noodle soup, with the highest possible spice (8), and I wasn‚Äôt disappointed. It was incredibly flavoursome, and it was actually spicy compared to a lot of other noodle soups in Paris. If you like chillis, go for this level! It doesn‚Äôt blow your head off, but leaves a lovely refreshing tingle and a warm mouth.

The Tsingtao beer alongside it was great, and the restaurant itself is lovely.

Thank you very much, I‚Äôll be back', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Flam&go
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "Very quant little Cafe. The decor is amazing. I had a gluten free soup that was lovely. They don't have a vegetarian option but they did have gluten free soup which was tasty... The green tea was lovely.
Wonderful atmosphere, very cozy and away from the rush in the stores..

The staff are young girls not very personable, so don't expect much from them but the place and food itself is lovely and definitely worth trying.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Nice place away from all the people. You have to order at the counter. As it was sunny, we enjoy our break outside. Too bad they had no espresso but the cakes were very good', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Cute little cafe to grab a quick bite‚Ä¶friendly people, beautiful views and great food‚Ä¶we had the svele and sognalapskaus‚Ä¶amazing!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Beautiful place, very cozy, wonderful views, and good bathroom. For a coffee place, it only has filtered coffee and no hot milk, and it wasn't very good. The cakes looked tasty but expensive. However, it has a wide range of dining dishes we didn't try.
Good peaceful place to hide from the rain, but coffee could be better.", 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Warm and cozy Kafe in middle of Fl√•m. It was the perfect ending to our trip to Fl√•m. We ordered some coffee, it was luke warm and when we asked for a hot coffee, the Kafe team was very friendly and served us hot coffee promptly and as a warm gesture we were offered chocholate cakes to make up for the coffee üòä', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Maison Louvard
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': "The crookie stole the show during my recent visit. This trendy fusion of croissant and cookie proved to be a flavorful delight, though a bit pricey for its size. While I didn't explore beyond this famed treat, the bakery's array of tempting options suggests it's a spot worth revisiting for those with a sweet tooth üòã", 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We called in for lunch and we were greeted by a very friendly waitress. We found the atmosphere to be excellent and very welcoming. Our waitress was very friendly and the food and service were superb. Braised beef cheek with seasonal vegetables and a terrine for starters were simply excellent. The wine was delicious too.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I tried the cookie croissant here few days ago. And it tastes as good as a regular croissant but 5 times more expensive, 7 times if you decide to take a table . Worth the hype? Not really.', 'rating': '2', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'ü§© crookie whaaaaat! I‚Äôve never had a cookie croissant ü•ê until today and I don‚Äôt think I can ever go back! Absolutely delicious, great cafe very vibrant and busy with lovely decor, perfect place to grab a morning coffee and treat!  As it‚Äôs quite popular service can be a bit slow but still well worth the visit', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "I saw this bakery on Social Media and was curious to know why people were given such a high rate to this place. I wanted to check it by myself üòâ The place is cozy and well decorated. The staff is super friendly and the 'viennoiserie' tasteful. The expresso is also really good and compared to other places in the capital, your getting a decent amount of coffee in your cup (not only a few drops). It was good, but wouldn't given them a 5 star rate (even if the bakker has apparently received an award recently). Guess I will have to go a second time (at lunch) to confirm my thoughts... A place to recommend anyhow.", 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Keopi
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Went there early and got a table. One can scan the QR code to see the menu with pictures. Great service and friendly staff. Definitely good place for brunch.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Delicious Korean brunch place! üá∞üá∑\U0001faf6üèº
We had to wait just a little bit for a table inside. It‚Äôs located in a little alley, easy to find if using Google maps.

Small menu but with lots of options!
We got the fried chicken, which tasted just perfect! Very soft on the inside and the seasonings was on point.
Salmon toast and salmon waffle which were both delicious.
The orange juice was very fresh and sweet.
Service was super fast! Friendly staff.
And most importantly, everything is HALAL!
(Expect for one thing which is the ‚Äúspam‚Äù)
Would definitely come back very soon!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'After watching their instagram account, I wanted to come here and try the brunch. It is an ‚Äúinstagramable‚Äù place, and as such, very popular so you‚Äôll have to wait. However, the waiting times are less than expected and it is worth it. The food is great and innovative. I had the waffle with fried chicken and it was delicious and abundant. The fried chicken is perfect and the sauce (sweet and spice) too, although it is not spicy.
The only problem was the time they took to bring our beverages. We ordered the homemade lemonade and we were almost finishing the dish when they brought it. We noticed the service of beverages is slow, so be patient.
In any case, I‚Äôd love to come back to try the sweet options.

üòãüåéüçΩÔ∏è‚úàÔ∏è
Sabor Kairos', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We went for brunch at 11:30 on a Sunday and waited for half an hour to be seated cause it was quite crowded. It was worth the wait though cause the staff were nice, service was alright and the food was delicious. We had waffles and they placed a bottle of maple syrup on every table.  I had rose tea and my friends had matcha flavoured drinks and they were all good. Reservations are not possible so avoiding peak times would be a good idea.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The location is simply great, not too far from the Grevin museum ! You really get to feel the parisian vibe.
The price was reasonable for a brunch + it was really delicious. The staff is also really nice and attentive.
We went for a kimchi and avocado salmon toast (which if you like salty and spicy kimchi is a perfect match with avocado and salmon). The Rose Latte was too die for with its hint of rose taste. The spicy chicken was really soft (a perfect boneless chicken if I dare say).
And for the dessert the waffle with matcha cream ! The cream paired perfectly with the fruits and the waffle ~ Beware though, the plate is kind of big so if you don‚Äôt have a big appetite it is best to share it.

All in all the pricing, the amount of food and the taste was more than worthy, a 10/10 for me.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Afri Call Food
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Food:

Place:

name: Boneshaker Donuts
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'All donuts are vegan which is amazing. But they were too sweet and greasy for me :/ I normally like desserts but this donut was too much in terms of sugar.

Plus, most of the donuts are 6‚Ç¨ each which I think is a bit overpriced. I tried the raspberry donut on Saint Valentine‚Äôs day so it was in a heart shape (cute ^_^). Again I know that donut is not an healthy thing, but I wished that at least there would be some healthier maybe less greasy options.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'As a vegan, I was thrilled to find a place that sells vegan donuts in Paris. All of their donuts are made daily from scratch and in house too. I had to try their traditional glaze one and a seasonal fall flavored one that was apple pie inspired. I almost felt guilty eating these as they tasted so good. I would have ordered more had I had more time. Staff spoke English which was super helpful. They were also very kind and passionate about their food which I found very inspiring. A definite must go to if you want good donuts in general!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': '100% vegan. The donuts were amazing. The hot chocolate was OK. The cashier seemed like she was stressed out. The total for the items in the picture was about 33 euros.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Hands down, these are the best donuts in Paris. I‚Äôve been coming here for years, and don‚Äôt plan on stopping anytime soon.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I am soo amazed that this place is vegan, you really can‚Äôt tell! The apple donut is autumn üçÇ in a donut ‚ô•Ô∏è so fluffy and amazing flavour combo!

The owners also are very cute and kind!

Will be back!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: OYA Fusion
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'It was not busy when we came. Service was excellent. Staff are quite attentive and pleasant. They seem to be joyful in serving people. name: Caf√© Louis Vuitton
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': "What a great place to sit after you have finished your visit at the Louis Vuitton Museum in a sunny but cold winter morning. The sweets are so beautiful, you just don't want to eat them. The place has a beautiful energy and atmosphere. Warm, though, with many windows and a great view of the river. The coffee is beautifully presented and the furniture is not too heavy. It is a really great place to visit as a continuation of a visit to the Louis Vuitton Museum, which is at the ground floor.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A great place to stop by after (or before) visiting the museum. A little overpriced but thats luxury brands for you haha, definitely worth a visit though. We went around 5:30pm on a Monday (early March) and we didn‚Äôt need to reserve or make a booking. The cakes and pastries were actually delicious and the staff were lovely.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'LV cafe was exceptionally good. I highly highly highly recommend making reservations. We made them for 12:30 pm and it wasn‚Äôt crowded and by the time we left at 3, there was at least 30 people waiting for a table. The food is not only beautiful, but so good. The eggs in particularly are really cool to try. And the desserts are so good. You can also do the LV dream experience after you eat!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent desserts and coffee!  Insanely overpriced?  Of course! What else would you expect.  Great service, great view out the windows at the Seine, and an unforgettable experience.  A must do after the Louvre or anytime!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Probably the most delicious cake I've ever ate! We got the chocolate and vanilla ones and they were amazing!\nPretty pricey, but understandable - it's Louis Vuitton!\nStaff was amazing, very friendly and very caring, smiling! Will definitely return when back in Paris", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: AC√Ä PIGALLE
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Definitely worth coming here. At first we thought food was going to suck since they microwave a lot of the dishes but it was one of the best meals. Taco meat was so tasty and their burrito was 5/5! Would love to come back here again!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We went for dinner without reservation, but even tho they were packed, they were able to give us a table.
We got a liter of margarita to go with our Ac√† nachos. They were crisp and the topping was guacamole, some pulled meat and cheddar. Overall very tasty and yummy.
For the entrees we got burritos with different meats, and all of them were up to our expectations. The portion was also good, didn‚Äôt leave anyone hungry.
The only thing we noticed was that it took some time to get the attention of the waiter to order the entrees, but they were really packed and everyone was running around, so it‚Äôs understandable.
Recommended if you are around the Moulin Rogue.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Authentic Mexican food.
Relaxed atmosphere with great music.
Service attentive and friendly.
Very popular place at lunchtime.
No reservations possible at this time. Here it is first come, first served!', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Really nice Tacos, a bit disappointed with my cantarito, which was adapted to Paris, a bit bitter instead sour and sweet. It is an amazing drink, anyway that you should try citric, refreshing and their version bitter.  I loved my nachos and my governor tacos(prawn).
The horchata will be 100% better if you make it natural.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Overall, is a good place to eat tacos considering you are in Paris. Formule of three tacos for 10‚Ç¨ is a great option. Good flavor in the barbacoa, pastor a little dry, and carnitas would improve with a little more coriander. Sauces are good and tasty, not super spicy. Agua de horchata is super good, not too sweat which I like.  However, the dessert, the pastel de tres leches, falls short of expectations. While sweet and pastry-like, it lacks the authentic essence of a true pastel de tres leches.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Rice & Burger Kitchen
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': "Tiny little place which is to be expected. Do not come here if you're looking for traditional sushi. At best it's fusion food, and in very tiny portions, at Parisian prices. You will leave here ready for an actual dinner.", 'rating': '2', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'It was so damn good and the service was great! They made a kind gesture for my birthday (most appreciated). The food was excellent. I recommend!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I absolutely love this place and keep going over and over again. Most delicious and fresh sushi‚Äôs, with flavors you won‚Äôt find anywhere else around. Very cool design and atmosphere too. Did I mention the very cute and adorable waiters? ;)', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Little busy restaurant even on weekday nights. Luckily we didn‚Äôt have to wait for a table. Staff were very welcoming and friendly. Nice atmosphere but as the restaurant is small, the tables are tiny and you have to squeeze everything in which was uncomfortable. The food was average, the sushis were okay but not exceptional. The teriyaki salmon bowl was a total let down. It‚Äôs not teriyaki salmon without the sauce?!, just a plain grilled piece of salmon. Quite disappointed!', 'rating': '2', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'nice staff ! unfortunately very subpar sushi. Tempura was ok - wet batter, a bit overcooked shrimp. but the nigiri we really couldn‚Äôt force ourselves to eat. Its the seasoning that they put in the rice that didn‚Äôt taste right, so only the fish was eaten (sans rice). i wish we took a pic of the sashimi, because the slices were cut so randomly and amateurish. for the taste and value, it‚Äôs a bit sad. We spent more than ‚Ç¨60 for just the two of us. The chinese sushi places are more preferable.', 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Puffy Cookies
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Best cookies I‚Äôve tried in Paris (and I‚Äôm extremely fussy with my cookies). They‚Äôre perfectly soft in the middle and ‚Äòmi-cuit‚Äô. They‚Äôre very balanced, not too sweet, the chocolate feels like it‚Äôs nice quality and same for the nuts that they use that are perfectly toasted and crunchy which gives a more interesting texture to the cookies. Can feel they put a bit of salt in the cookies which I appreciate. They definitely don‚Äôt taste like fake vanilla. Very very generously sized and I love all their branding! I think the posters inside are really well done. My favourite cookie was the chocolate and hazelnut one. My boyfriend‚Äôs favourite was the dark chocolate one!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Do you wanna try the best cookies in Paris??? Run here. Perfectly soft on the inside. Wide range of options. Prices are decent. Open every day. Perfect.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The best cookies in Paris!

These cookies are gooey and soft but yet still crunchy on the outside.

The staff were very nice and gave recommendations. The cookies are a bit more than your average cookie but it is worth it.

I paid 7.50‚Ç¨ for two cookies.

If you‚Äôre visiting Paris definitely make a trip to get these cookies!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Cookies are to die for (levain bakery NYC style!) coffee really good, and milkshake is a killer ü§§ plus the service is super friendly, and you have some inside space to enjoy your calories intake', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This is not a normal cookie, it‚Äôs thick and gooey. The chocolate and peanut butter one was my favourite.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Maison Ma√©
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'My favourite bakery in Paris. My everyday breakfast was here during my trip. The croissants are the best. And the apple pies are the best of the best. The jam in the pie is so good, not too sour, not too sweet. Everything is just fine. The owners are really nice people also. One nice lady, with two handsome boys. Wish i could take everything here with me back to Shanghai.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I came for breakfast all three mornings that I stayed in Paris and I must say that I could not have found anything better. From the friendly and lovable staff (who even gave me a croissant on the last day when they saw me with my luggage) to the pastries that were simply delicious.
I will definitely return when I have the opportunity to revisit the city.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This is a really nice local coffee place with fresh bakery and desserts. The lovely staff is very helpful and friendly who doesnt mind go the extra mile to help a customer. Everything in the menu is priceful here.
The welcoming smile from them, with the tasteful croissants/pastries and quality hot coffees and the small but warm atmosphere is an obvious five star rate.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing croissants, pain au chocolat is to die for‚Ä¶ loving this bakery and the hosts are very lovely and pleasant ü§óü§óü§ó
We recommend it with our hearts ‚ò∫Ô∏è', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'My 3 friends and I are visiting Paris as Americans for the first time and this cafe is the most amazing part of Paris. Friendly staff, who have been helping us with our French, tasty food at a reasonable price, and a relaxing atmosphere. We‚Äôve come here every morning and will definitely come again the next time we visit! I‚Äôd recommend the ham escargot and the espresso! They also gave our group free pastries sometimes :)', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Kous
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'This "bar" is a take-away for couscous.
The choice of vegetables and meats is wide and the quality excellent.
However, like everything in Paris the prices are relatively steep.
For 3 persons, couscous with mixed meats, will cost about 45 Euro.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Marocco food is amazing and also cheap for size M ‚Ç¨14 u can share also( I‚Äôm Asian so for me the portion is quite big );) it‚Äôs good for health and diet. Recommend place for lunch', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very tasty and fast couscous at a reasonable price! The lamb one (Tanjia) in particular is delicious! Perfect place for lunch breaks', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'They have been their for over 6 years worth a visit!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This place was THE BEST! I met the owner Bader and he was super nice. A must try if you‚Äôre in Paris!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Kous
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'I happened to stop by this place by coincidence and I am happy I did. The place is small and the food is good. I tried the Tanjia couscous and I did love it. This is important as I am not a couscous person by default and hate the exaggerated spices or the pool of liquids on my food. The staff are polite and attentive.

What caught my eye was the level of anticipations to the needs of clients

1- You can chose size of your plate, depending how hungry you are.

2- for first time I saw in my life that a restaurant also includes feminine hygiene pad also in the toilet.

Bravo for that , a good customer service wins .

I do recommend the place for those whom like to have a nice healthy food. I will eat there again while am in Paris.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent couscous!  Several offerings. Vegetarian, meats, vegan. Choices of classic or whole wheat grain (couscous). Super fresh. Delicious mint tea & small North African pastries. Friendly service. Lovely setting in a modern North African style. Try it. You will not regret it.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "We're always a fan of Morrocan cuisine, and KOUS did not disappoint. Try the soup before your main dish, and get a cup of hot tea - you'll be glad you did.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A very pleasant place to eat a good, satisfying couscous, delicious mint tea and pastry and very tasty appetizer. The staff is very welcoming and obliging. I will definitely go back.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'So good', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: CHEZ HAKI
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "Went with my girlfriend; we enjoyed the ravioli and Nems starters, both worth trying.

Unfortunately, the main dishes fell short. The Poulet Croustillant noodles lacked flavor, were excessively greasy, and the chicken was merely okay.

Riz loc-lac had dry rice, chewy beef, mainly fat.

Hoping to give the benefit of the doubt, we visited at 4 PM, but suspect the dishes weren't freshly made‚Äîmicrowave sounds and quick service raised concerns.", 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Good overall, good quality-price ratio, vegetarian lamen did not reach the highest expectations (noodles were very good, the broth could have a bit more flavor), but very large portion size, and definitely better than a lot of places in France.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We discovered this restaurant while on a walk and decided to try right then and there. The gyoza was fab and we also enjoyed the soup ramen. I ordered the fried chicken cutlet noodles for myself but the serving was pretty big and would actually be enough for two people. We shall return.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very busy Chinese restaurant with nice expedite staff and extremely fast turnaround. Food was good and overall a very authentic Chinese restaurant experience.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The food was incredible. Tender noodles with the perfect chew with rich delicious broth. We loved the S7! The service was excellent and the atmosphere cozy. A perfect rich and hearty meal at very reasonable prices especially for the flavor, portions, and quality.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Bao Express
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'If you looking for the correct style of food. Sorry, it is not. Fancy enough but nothing related to the food.

Their service was super quick, my dishes were delivered within 5 minutes after my order. All the food were cold when they arrivd my table.

Not tasty enough. The bun meat was dry and small portion, which a qualified meat bun shoul be meaty with juice. This style Chinese food should serve in hot and not pre cook.

At last, I am questioning about how the meat bun was made. You can saw that the bamboo steamer was dry compared to the Siumai one. The Siumai steamer was wet that mean at least the Siumai was steamed in it. Anyway, it was only my observation but mean nothing.', 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I loved this place! In two weeks took the following: Chinese spring rolls (they were ok), Xiao Long Bao Shangai classic (the filling is very good and the dough is thick and fluffy), Char Siu Bao (basically the big dumplings, they are super tasty, I preferred these to the smaller ones), Aubergines Hong Shao (for sure the best thing we ate, they were delicious, I sincerely recommend these) and finally the Poulet Sweet & Sour (very good as well). We were very hungry and in the end we were quite full. Plus, the service was super kind and welcoming.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very very overrated, you can find better asian
restaurants in Paris. Never order the lemonade, it is just water. The mango sago is a mango lassi with very few tapioca perles and some small chunks of mango. Aubergines and noodles are ok.
Service was great. A shame that food wasn‚Äôt as good. Everything is deeply fried.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Loved this great place. üòã
Great food, options even for vegans.
Big place so you can be spontaneous, friendly staff.
Enjoy', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This has to be one of THE HIDDEN GEMS of Paris. This isn‚Äôt on any tourist lists of places to eat and it‚Äôs not typical French food, but it is delicious and the vibe in this place is immaculate. We enjoyed it so much, we went back on our last night in Paris to have it again!  Beef Ho Fun is easily the best dish we had in Paris and the Sweet and Sour Chicken is unlike any version we‚Äôve had in the best way possible. Also, if you‚Äôre a dessert person, the lava French toast is a must try!  We would eat here again and again and will recommend this place to anyone traveling to Paris!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Taco Mesa

reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Most creative gyozas I tried in Paris.

name: RAMEN WANG
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "This is the most delicious ramen I have ever tasted in Paris. It reminds me of the ramen in Tokyo that I missed so much. Fast service, polite staff. Clean and comfortable. There may be a line outside, but it's worth the wait. I'm glad I found this place", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing place! Very good food and good service and fair prices. Every Tuesday they have vegan ramen. Would definitely come back', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I‚Äôve had ramen in Hong Kong and Tokyo and this is definitely one of my favourites of all time. We‚Äôve been several times, at different times of the day and days of the week yet the food has been amazingly consistent every single time.

The pork is their speciality and spectacular, every bite makes me so happy. The soup is always flavoursome and balanced.

Unfortunately they don‚Äôt take booking in advance so you have to queue. One time we went with our friends (~about 8 of us in total) after our wedding and we had to wait a long time as there was a lot of us but as the food was so tasty, people forgot about the long wait.

All of the staff are friendly, wonderful and attentive and it‚Äôs always a pleasure to come here.

While it‚Äôs growing in popularity, I hope it‚Äôll stay consistent and continue to be a gem in the 14th arrondissement.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Loved to eat with you. Just needed to wait some minutes outside. But was worth it!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Everything was delicious! Ramen was amazing with lots of flavors. The veggie gyozas as appetizers were tasty too. Nice variety of desserts and I really recommend the matcha financiers with ginger ice cream. Nice wine by the glass as well. Very cozy venue and ambience. A must!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: LiBeyrouth
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'I have no complaints about the taste of the food, but I feel it is overpriced for the range of items we get there I have been to few Indian buffets which offer a huge range of items when compared to this with the same price. We waited for 15 mins I guess just to get in and the place was very compact. I even had to wait to refill my plate. The toilet was extremely untidy, with no toilet paper and hand wash. "Please at least keep your toilet clean for customers my sincere request to you".', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Within four years, I have eaten here four times. As always, a dream! Simple Lebanese dishes prepared with love. My favorite is parsley salad with tomatoes and eggplant salad! Chicken is also seasoned great! Everything tastes good! Small but nice. Thank you, I will come back!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "üòãVery effective Lebanese all you can eat buffet with tasty dishes. The selection is small but well prepared, there is a cold and warm selection. Their cuisine is fresh and full of flavor.

‚ö†Ô∏èThe place is popular so it gets crowded easily with a waiting queue outside in the evening !

üòï The downsides :
- Toilets are on the outside, so if its rainy its not rly convenient..
- The limited space : they dont take reservations so forget it if you're planning to be in a group bigger than 4 people unless you're willing to wait a lot outside.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The staff is very friendly and the food was very good. We had the chance to taste every plate and all of them was tasty.
We paid 19,99 for a ‚ÄúAll you can eat‚Äù.

I completely recommend this restaurant.

Also, make sure to come early otherwise you will queue for a long time. (We waited 1h).', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We went for the 20‚Ç¨ buffet and there was a long queue but we decided to wait. name: Plan D - DWICH & GLACE
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Yeah, it‚Äôs a stone cold 5 stars. Incredible food, location is great, you can easily sit beside the canal and eat (since it‚Äôs really a tiny bar set up inside), prices super reasonable, staff were friendly and have superhuman memory for who ordered what. One note: it‚Äôs popular and busy, so plan to queue and wait for food. Totally worth it tho.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We came by for lunch. this is a tiny deli type restaurant. You only have a bar to sit. Menu consists of two sandwiches and 2 sides and desserts. I think it regularly changes. We took the mushroom sandwich (le brun), fries, and salad with sesame vinaigrette sauce. Honestly everything was perfect. The sandwich was phenomenal. Also unrelated maybe but everyone working there that day was super beautiful/handsome so both your stomach and your eyes have a feast üëâüèªüëàüèªüòå', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'BEST PLACE ON EARTH.
I am not kidding, I think I go there at lease once a month. They make the tastiest, most flavorful sandwiches you‚Äôll ever have. And everything is vegan. They are politically, ethically, socially engaged. The staff is the nicest.
Sandwich choices are a rotation of 2 seasonal recipes.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing sandwiches and lovely staff. Could not recommend more.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Plan D is a haven for vegetarian/vegan sandwich enthusiasts.

name: Mopa
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Awesome vegan place with really filling and tasty food! We tried the arancini, cold beast burger, and doner kebab. name: Jungle Palace
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Overall the experience is good!

We came here for the theme, and it delivers!

We were serviced by Agathe, she is very nice! Quick and friendly service was offer and she is very responsive towards our requests.

The food portion is smaller than expected, the taco that we ordered turns out only have two pieces.

Veggie curry feels too simple since it mainly consists two types of veggie. It would be great if more varieties are offered.

The fish were really cool.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A different culinary experience with music, sounds and special effects. Very original and worth a visit!', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Wow just wow! Our server was so kind and very attentive too.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great experience and excellent setting. Overall the staff was great  ( warm welcome and friendly ) except for one female waitress who wasn‚Äôt friendly at all and looked annoyed the entire evening. Thankfully her colleague was funny and a great contrast ! )', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Def must visit , loved the ambience and the Pulled Pork Burger was amazing .also recommend the eggplant for starter !!! name: Maslow - Restaurant Paris 1
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Been wanting to go for ages now and so glad we went ! Lovely vibes, lovely and quite big , airy restaurant that is relaxed yet professional, friendly service. Boyfriend and I took the fixed lunch menu at 19 euros. His ≈ìuf parfaits with brioche was absolutely delicious and my vegetarian donburi dish( breaded mushroom) was good but not outstanding . The choux √† la cr√®me ( caramelized puff pastry with  salted caramel and cream center hit the spot and the coffee was fine . We will be back üôèüå∏', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Out of my Michelin Stars Challenges (follow me for all the reviews on every Michelin Stars in Paris and more‚Ä¶ way more), I try non Michelin but mainly veggie places thanks to a good friend who is vegetarian. The sound level due to the design is quite high (especially compared to my usual Michelin star‚Ä¶) but it‚Äôs the price to pay to go in a very lively place.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "We arrived after seeing its great reviews but not realizing it was a vegetarian restaurant.  They asked if we had reservations, we didn't, but they still accommodated us.  We ordered the squash (my favorite) the cauliflower wings (my friends favorite) and the gnocchi (mushroom forward and delicious).  I also tried the BSA mocktail. A delicious and refreshing lemon tart drink that went very well with the meal.  As someone who wouldn't normally seek a vegetarian restaurant, I left feeling very satisfied and full and I'm still craving more of that incredible squash.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The place is really chic and has a great vibe. reviews:
